I came into the game wanting everyone to win, mostly as it seemed like the most assured path to getting the most coins for myself. I was concerned when I saw there was a 'free rider effect' going on with someone consistently choosing to keep the coin. And it make me think that the solidarity of players choosing to invest in Allshire just wouldn't last. I then succumbed to my own selfish thinking, I was frustrated that the other players were keeping coins and not investing so I just started to do the same. My strategy wasn't always consistent, I would see that a Westville player was investing in Westville again and so the next round I would do the same but it would be too late and that person had gone back to hoarding coins. I felt like my team Westville weren't as cohesive as Eastburgh and they had a better team dynamic. From the start I thought choosing Allshire felt like the most honest option, I was also concerned that once any of the other players had started to feel like they were being 'screwed' by the other players then it would spark vengeful or selfish activity that would be impossible to come back from. Indeed that seems to be what happened. In hindsight I wish I had been one of the free riders at the start of the game who kept coins and benefitted from the Allshire investment, but I think I don't have it in me to cheat other people even in an anonymous online game.
I felt annoyed that one player in our group kept getting more coins as they kept it for themselves and got a bonus as me and another player were cooperating!
